\title{FIFO scheduling}

\p{First-in, first-out. Jobs are run to completion in the order they arrive. Trivially fair under any reasonable notion of fairness, but suffers from the \em{convoy effect}: a single long-running job at the head delays every shorter job behind it, inflating average turnaround time.}

\problem{If the first arriving job is much longer than the rest, all subsequent jobs wait at least its full duration before getting any CPU.}
